# Production Environment Variables Template
#
# IMPORTANT: This file documents the REQUIRED environment variables for production.
# DO NOT fill in actual values here - configure these in your deployment platform.
#
# @see OPS-012: CONFIG_SECURITY - Environment-specific configs with placeholders
# @see SEC-016: SECRET_MANAGEMENT - Load secrets from vault/environment at runtime
# @see OPS-004: DEPLOYMENT_SECURITY - Production deployment configuration

# =============================================================================
# REQUIRED: API Configuration
# =============================================================================
# Production backend API URL
# Example: https://api.nuvanaapp.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_BACKEND_URL=${PRODUCTION_API_URL}

# Legacy variable - set to same value as NEXT_PUBLIC_BACKEND_URL
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=${PRODUCTION_API_URL}

# =============================================================================
# REQUIRED: Database Configuration
# =============================================================================
# Production database connection string
# MUST be loaded from secrets manager (AWS Secrets Manager, Vault, etc.)
# Format: postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@HOST:PORT/DATABASE?connection_limit=20
DATABASE_URL=${DATABASE_SECRET_FROM_VAULT}

# =============================================================================
# REQUIRED: Security Configuration (if using Next.js API routes)
# =============================================================================
# JWT secrets - MUST be loaded from secrets manager
# Minimum 32 characters, cryptographically random
# JWT_SECRET=${JWT_SECRET_FROM_VAULT}
# JWT_REFRESH_SECRET=${JWT_REFRESH_SECRET_FROM_VAULT}

# =============================================================================
# Production Checklist
# =============================================================================
# Before deploying to production, ensure:
#
# [ ] All secrets are stored in a secrets manager (not in this file)
# [ ] NEXT_PUBLIC_BACKEND_URL points to your production API
# [ ] Database connection uses SSL (add ?sslmode=require to DATABASE_URL)
# [ ] CORS_ORIGIN on backend matches your frontend domain
# [ ] All environment variables are set in deployment platform
# [ ] No development/test values are used in production
#
# Nuvana Production URLs:
# - Frontend: https://nuvanaapp.com (or your domain)
# - API: https://api.nuvanaapp.com
